title: Unique and wild
text: Great place to visit to see the amazing blue water, ruggared rocks, whitest sand and not crowded. Isolated so bring what you need

title: Amazing
text: Great place to visit. Saw heaps of orcas. Make sure you take tablets if prone to seasick. Ocean is rough even on a good day. Lots of food included for yhose who eat! No flash but wholesome and plentiful. Cost is high but it is a long way off sure.

title: Personal Tour at our pace
text: Having your own driver was not much dearer than taking a tour bus for two people. it made it flexible and at our pace. We had a driver who was as good as a tour guide
place: Private Day Trip to Canal,Ancient Corinth,Myceane and Nauplion

title: One of the Better Dams in WA
text: Canning Dam is pretty large. Sadly we dont get enough rain to make it exciting. If you want the classic WA dam with the best interests, go to Mundaring Weir. not as big but more historic and spectacular.

title: Best in Winter
text: This man-made regatta center is something WA can be proud of in that is does its functions well. however there is no natural flow of water so in summer it is a getting a little on the stagnant side.

title: Amazingly Clean and well cared for
text: I love a good reptile encounter and this one is great. The place has a very high standard of care and cleanliness. The animals are great. Dont forget the birds too!

title: Fascinating history
text: if you like history its worth a visit. The country had telegraph relay stations to help transmit messages - this was one of the more interesting remote area places.
place: Alice Springs Telegraph Station Historical Reserve

title: Nice views if not a dust bowl
text: In Summer if it is windy the dust is bad. On calm and clear day work the sunset or sunrise tour if you can make it.

title: Short walk good but not in Summer
text: Had a work trip so wanted a walk. Even in the morning it was pretty hot. Pick your time but the place is pretty impressive.

title: Comprehensive Breakfast
text: Good breakfast if you are staying at the crowne hotel. big spread for an Australian hotel. All tastes covered!

title: Nice hotel, bit tired
text: The hotel is on the other side of the Todd River to the township. In its day it was probably a grand resort, now its good. They try hard to make it comfortable. It was clean and breakfast was pretty good for a hotel. If you have a hire car it is a good location.

title: A Pretty Good Harbour
text: I like harbours and this one with the old battlements, international sailors, and ferries was pretty good. loved the old guys fishing and the cats on the rocks.

title: Unique
text: Fascinating to walk down the street of knights where for 200 years the knights of ST John operated for the crusaders. beautiful architecture.

title: Interesting but not exceptional
text: There are many acropolis in Greece and this was not the most exciting one to visit. A quick trip was interesting.

title: Wow a real castle
text: The knights of St John were here for 200 years helping the crusades. The history is interesting and you get to see a real castle!

title: Great Piece of History
text: It was fascinatiing to this site and museum due to the mix of Roman and Greek influence with a touch of earlier history present. Worth the trip if you like hisotry
place: Ancient Corinth and Daphni Monastery Half-Day Tour from Athens

title: Sad and tired
text: I love fish but this place needs a serious overhaul. Half the creatures were covered in slime. It was fish prison. I came out depressed.

title: Good for summer
text: Being Australian we have beaches. This was good for Greece but I wouldn't want to be here in simmer. You could not move!

title: Great museum
text: This was a great museum to visit. The buildings are pretty special in this area so is the history of the knights.
place: Archaeological Museum of Rhodes (Hospital of the Knights)

title: Spectacular
text: Great site to visit. The climb is steep but worth it. I think it is iconic. The town is cute. Great in off season

title: Magnificant
text: What an amazing place to visit. The ST John knights were busy in their 200 years on Rhodes and this history is etched into the city. Beautiful!
place: Palace of the Grand Master of the Knights of Rhodes

title: Amazing
text: This an impressive archaeological site from about 2000 Bc. The recovery of the ruins impressive. Go Greece!

title: What Beach? in winter
text: Red beach in the off season is barely there. WE had some surf coming in so the beach could not be accessed. From the point it still looked good!

title: Most interesting
text: A local museum containing only items found at the site. Beautifully presented and interesting. Must do it!

title: Fascinating history
text: This the center of the Greek universe for the ancients. It is amazing place to visit. Its in the mountains so bring an extra layer.

title: History worth seeing
text: The crowds even in november were busy but the site worth seeing. Cant visit greece without coming here.

title: Unexpectedly interesting
text: The first olympic stadium to a nonsport person seemed unlikely to be interesting but it was a fascinating half hour exploring. Loved the old Olympic flames and the tunnel

title: Great artifacts
text: Big museum with some great artifacts. Loved the gold displays including the sad death foils of an infant. The beauty and form exhibition was great. Bit too many damaged relics on display so gets bit tedious in places

title: Great location small rooms
text: Great location. Loved where it is for historic sites and shopping. Space in athens is limited so rooms are tiny. Bed is big. The rooms are clean and included breakfast is pretty good for a free meal. Recommended!

title: Rushed and poor quality
text: You want to eat out but here they want to get fed to clear the table. The food was really not cooked with love. Seemed to be reheat and no style. I am not a harsh critic but they deserve two.

title: History in real time
text: Amazing place to visit. History which you have read and seen you can walk around. It was being repaired so you had to angle to get the photo with out scaffolding and cranes

title: Ancient Ruin worth seeing
text: I love things ancient and this does not disappoint. It is well policed so do not go out of fenced areas or you will be whistled and told off. The area is an easy walk but the rocks bit slippery if its rained.

title: Cheap fun and nice view
text: It is a must do in wellington and while it is not a spectacular cable car it is please ride to the scenic view of the top of hiill. The walk down is nice - about 30 minutes

title: Pretty as a picture
text: Those waterfalls are not huge but it is a pretty place to visit. Good boardwalks to access the better views

title: Catch the trout!
text: The Vasse trout farm has a big lake to fish. You can catch your dinner. You pay for your catch but its a good couple of hours.

title: Even without a 4 wheel drive you can visit
text: These dunes are worth a visit. Like a white sand desert in the in the middle of the forest. If you have a big four wheel drive you can drive there but in a normal car park at the lake and walk the 1.2 km - its not hard walk.

title: Windy harbour and cliffs
text: Teh amazing cliffs off the Windy Harbour point is pretty special. Worth the drive and the hill top walks are good.

title: Nice place
text: For a local national park it was okay to visit. The Gloucester tree is a good place to climb. Love the trees.

title: Best tree house ever!
text: The bicentennial tree is one of three fire lookouts and still open to public climbing. Nowhere else in the world can you climb the outside of the tree to 68 meters. one day you will have to have safety harnesses but not yet!

title: Bit old but very well equipped
text: The forest lodge had one of the very best equip chalets I have stayed in right down to a milk frother. The people who run it keep in clean and tidy. The location is close to town, you can even walk to the Gloucester Tree. The heating works a treat which is important in a WA southwest. Kangaroos on the lawn.

title: Great views
text: This place had great views on the one clesr day we got. Sadly Toronto seems to be growing up with an ugly sprawl. It seems to have lost its unique culture. Sad really.

title: Good quality hotel
text: I dont usually review hotels but was impressed with the staff and service. Helpful to me. Ensured i had a quiet room after my long flight. Easy to have extended late checkout. It was clean and confortable

title: Better in Canada
text: I went the falls years ago from the USA side and was not particularly impressed. This time i was on the canada side and felt it was way more impressive. I am australian so this not an USA vs Ca opinion.

title: Bit overrated but okay
text: After standing in lines for ages you get to walk a few tunnels. I enjoyed the thundering vibration mor than the actual views. I must admit that looking up at the falls from the bottom was cool.

title: Not quite silver
text: This a beautiful temple. The silver is floor tiles but covered in carpet. The statues are impressive but not sure they are as gold as they say. Call me cynical.

title: Must see
text: Around Seim Reap there are some great sites and Angkor Thom is certainly one of them. worth looking into some further afield like Beng Mealea

title: Best before visiting Angkor sites
text: If you want to understand some of the complex history of this area to make better sense of what you are seeing, do the museum tour. Open to 6.30 pm it gives you an orientation to the kings and religion which made the area. Hindu, Buddhist, Hindu, Buddhist - you can make sense of some of the complexity of what you are seeing.

title: Pick your timing
text: Wow - worth flying around the world to see. The center piece is the tower of 65 meters. Only a 100 people at at time. Worth the climb but we had to queue for an hour. Either try off peak or beat the Chinese tour buses!

title: Great Visit
text: This place has many buddha with their faces attached still but when hindu ruler took over put on the magic eye. Interesting mix of culturess

title: A shining light
text: In a city with markets and stalls all around this one actually has some local product making it worth a visit. We found there to be less hard sell and a sense of fun. I nice add-on is several of the girls serving in the shops were deaf - in a country with no social security it is nice touch.

title: Burboun St in Cambodia
text: This little street has cute small local bars bit like Burboun street in new orleans. If you like a small bar, have a visit

title: Great NIght Out
text: Whizzing around Phnom Phen on vespa to highlight landmarks, good food, and for those who drink, another drink, then this a tour for you. As mature couple we found it still a thrill to be out on the Vespas. The staff were helpful and the night well organised. Especially good if you are newly arrived in the city.

title: Deeply Disturbing reflection of human behavour
text: In the 1970's Pol Pot had control of the country for 4 years and killed a quarter of the population for being intellectual, rich, city dwelling, wearing glasses, or allegedly conspiring against his regime. Bullets were too expensive for truck loads of people were bludgeoned to death at killing fields. This one is one kept for remembrance. Dont need a tour. At $15 half day tuktuk will take you out and the headset will tell you all you need to know!

title: Depressing but worthwhile
text: This is the S21 prison site from the Cambodian Pol Pot regime. It is equal to visiting some of the Jewish holocaust sites as far as disturbing goes. This was school turned to torture centre. Dont need to pay for a formal tour. A $2 tuktuk will get you there and the headset tour will tell you all you need.

title: Should be called National Buddist Museum
text: This was a short but interesting visit. It is national museum but mostly about Buddhist artefacts. you need to go to the genocide museum to appreciate what this country has experienced

title: great little temple
text: there are many temples in buddist countries. this one was a pretty well cared for temple and a pleasure to visit

title: Another big market
text: Central market is easy to get to by tuk-tuk. once there it is big. you can get anything from motorcycle tyres to seafood. the food section is scary by western health standards but quite interesting. the sellers are not pushy like in Bali or Malaysia.
